Three young men who disarmed a gunman on a high-speed train bound for Paris will get a heroes\' welcome in their hometown in California. Sacramento Mayor Kevin Johnson tweeted \"We are throwing a parade for our 3 hometown heroes!\" The state capital will strike up the bands for student Anthony Sadler, 22, Spencer Stone, a 23-year-old U.S. airman, and National Guardsman Alek Skarlatos, 22. At Sacramento State University, where Sadler is a senior. President Robert S. Nelsen said he looked forward to thanking the kinesiology major in person when he returns to class.

